children.subject: I don't think I follow your question... are you asking why you were enrolled in the course?

Yeah. Essentially, I have 2 (general) questions.

1. If I am looking for a class and see that the class is open, can I waitlist for a discussion/lab? If I do waitlist for it, will I be enrolled if someone drops the discussion/lab?

2. I was already enrolled in the class and I was in a lab. I decided to switch to another lab. The lab I wanted was closed until one night, and during that night it opened with 1 spot available and a full waitlist. How come I was able to switch into that lab when there was a waitlist (there are still seats available in 61b)

1) Yes

2) I suppose it's possible that everyone on the waitlist fell outside of the categories listed on this website, so you were able to fill the open spot.
Sorry I meant lab for every place where I said discussion.

history.content:
I'm not sure if this has been asked yet, but I have a huge question on waitlists.

I know people say to waitlist for the discussion section that is more open to get a seat in the class, but if there are seats available in lecture, can you waitlist for a discussion?

If the class is open but there's a waitlist for a discussion, how does that get processed? I just switched into a section that had 1 available seat (I was enrolled in the class and the class is still open (cs61b)), and I was automatically switched into it, but the section has a full waitlist, so why was I admitted but not the first waitlisted student?
